This paper is about mining security posts from developer Q&A websites using a novel learning framework. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which suggest possible categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper is relevant to software engineering and development, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category.
